results.name: Number of non-isomorphic intersecting set-systems of weight n with no singletons.
comment: An intersecting set-system is a finite set of finite nonempty sets (edges), any two of which have a nonempty intersection. The weight of a set-system is the sum of cardinalities of its elements. Weight is generally not the same as number of vertices.
